d of Hollywood's commercial imperatives. An invaluable resource to the film student, critic, and fan, Second Takes offers new ways of looking at the film sequel's industrial, aesthetic, cultural, political, and theoretical contexts.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aFilm sequels. 0aFilm series. 4aCultural Studies : Popular Culture. 4aFilm, Visual Culture, and Performing Arts : Film Studies. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / History & Criticism.2bisacsh1 aForrest, Jennifer, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGoggin, Joyce, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHark, Ina Rae, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHerbert, Daniel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJess-Cooke, Carolyn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJess-Cooke, Carolyn, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLeitch, Thomas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcEnteggart, Simon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPalmer, R. Barton, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPerkins, Claire, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRombes, Nicholas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSutton, Paul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVerevis, Constantine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVerevis, Constantine, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438430317423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter